Task 2: Create a Dockerfile for a Sample Project
Application Choice
For this task, I selected a Node.js application that serves a basic web page.

Dockerfile Implementation
Dockerfile
# Use the official Node.js image as base
FROM node:18-slim
# Set the working directory
WORKDIR /app
# Copy the application source code
COPY index.js .
# Expose the application port
EXPOSE 8080
# Command to run the application
CMD ["node", "index.js"]

Build and Verification Commands
Build: docker build -t learningwithjunoon/sample-app:latest .
Run: docker run -d -p 8080:80 learningwithjunoon/sample-app:latest
Verify Status: docker ps
Logs: docker logs <container_id>

