Task 4: Optimize Your Docker Image with Multi-Stage Builds
Multi-Stage Dockerfile

Dockerfile
# Stage 1: Build
FROM node:20-slim AS builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY index.js .
# Stage 2: Final minimal image
FROM node:20-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=builder /app/index.js .
EXPOSE 8080
CMD ["node", "index.js"]

Image Size Comparison
Task 2 Image (Single Stage): 192 MB
Task 4 Image (Multi-Stage Alpine): 54 MB
Improvement: The image size was reduced by approximately 72% by using a multi-stage approach and a minimal Alpine base image.

