Task 6: Persist Data with Docker Volumes

Implementation
Create Volume: docker volume create my_volume
Run Container with Volume: docker run -d -v my_volume:/app/data learningwithjunoon/sample-app:v1.0

Importance of Volumes
Docker volumes allow data to persist even if a container is deleted or recreated.
They are essential for databases and stateful applications where data loss is not an option.

