Task 7: Configure Docker Networking

Implementation
Create Network: docker network create my_network
Run App and Database on same network:
docker run -d --name sample-app --network my_network learningwithjunoon/sample-app:v1.0
docker run -d --name my-db --network my_network -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root mysql:latest

Communication Significance
Docker networking enables service discovery, allowing containers to communicate using their names (e.g., my-db)
instead of static IP addresses, which is vital for multi-container microservices.

