Task 10: Critical Reflection

Docker is an essential tool in modern software development. 
It provides the portability and consistency required for agile teams.
By mastering multi-stage builds, I have learned to produce images that are not only small and efficient but also significantly more secure.

The main challenge encountered during this project was a port conflict on 8080,
which was resolved by identifying and terminating the local process using lsof and kill.
This underscored the importance of understanding the interaction between the Docker daemon and the host operating system.


